OL,7,FHowever, the deputy minister for
OL,8,Fclimate change added: "By and large,
OL,9,Fpeople are driving slower."
OL,11,FSharp End presenter Rob Osborne
OL,12,Fresponded by suggesting it had "never"
OL,13,Fbeen a question of people driving
OL,14,Fslower as they will "obey the law."
OL,16,FThe programme also examined abuse
OL,17,Ffaced by politicians. found three
OL,18,Fquarters of Welsh MSs and MPs who
OL,19,Fresponded felt unsafe as a result of
OL,20,Ftheir role.
